nly major Western-language work on this subject and a landmark not only in Japanese history, but in the history of the environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aForest policyxJapan. 0aForest policyzJapan. 0aForests and forestryxJapan. 0aForests and forestryzJapan. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aafforestation.  aarchipelago.  acentral japan.  aconservation.  aecology.  aecosystem.  aedo period.  aenvironment.  aexploitation forestry.  aforest regulation.  aforest terrain.  aforestry.  ahumans and nature.  aindustrialism.  aindustrialized society.  ajapan.  akinai basin.  aland use patterns.  aland use.  amedieval japan.  anational forests.  anatural world.  anature preserve.  anature.  aplantation forestry.  apreindustrial.  aprivate land.  aregenerative forestry.  asilviculture.  atimber depletion.  atimber.  atokugawa.  awilderness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052090876540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520908765423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520908765/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles